         <abstract>
            <p>The <foreign xml:lang="gez">Maṣḥafa ṭomār</foreign> narrates how a letter urging the people to respect the Sunday rest appeared outside a Church of Rome in which the patriarch Athanasius celebrated mass.
         </p>
            <p>There exists a short version (most frequent) and a long version, the latter begins with መጽሐፈ፡ ጦማር፡ ዘወረደትት፡ እምሰማይ፡ ላዕለ፡ እደ፡
               አትናቴዎስ</p>
         </abstract>
